org.matsim.core.replanning

Interface GenericPlanStrategy<T extends BasicPlan,I>

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    PlanStrategy
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    GenericPlanStrategyImpl, PlanStrategyImpl

    public interface GenericPlanStrategy<T extends BasicPlan,I>
    Notes:
    • If an implementation of this interface is "innovative", i.e. modifies plans, then it should first copy that plan, add the new plan to the choice set, and then modify that new copy. Otherwise, the evolutionary functionality of MATSim will probably be destroyed. kai, jan'15
    Author:
    (of the generic version) Kai Nagel

    • Method Detail

      • run

        void run(HasPlansAndId<T,I> person)
        Adds a person to this strategy to be handled. It is not required that the person is immediately handled during this method-call (e.g. when using multi-threaded strategy-modules). This method ensures that an unscored plan is selected if the person has such a plan ("optimistic behavior").
        Parameters:
        person -
        See Also:
        finish()

        void init(ReplanningContext replanningContext)
        Tells this strategy to initialize its modules. Called before a bunch of person are handed to this strategy.
